Country Dashboards Global On this page üåç SunCulture Dashboard ‚Äì Global Welcome to the Global Dashboard, which aggregates key KPIs across SunCulture‚Äôs operations in Uganda, Kenya, and C√¥te d‚ÄôIvoire (CIV) to provide a unified performance view. üéØ Objective‚Äã The Global Dashboard aims to: Consolidate key KPIs from Kenya, Uganda, and CIV at a global level. Enable cross-country comparisons for decision-making and strategic alignment. üìà Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)‚Äã Below are the KPIs tracked globally, including their business relevance, calculation logic, and caveats. 1. üíº Sales (YTD)‚Äã Purpose: Displays total unit sales year-to-date, compares performance to budgets/targets, and breaks down sales by country and department (Field Sales, SSC, Telesales, BD). Calculation: Kenya & CIV: Cash clients: Use Full Payment Date PAYG clients: Use Full Deposit Date Uganda: Cash clients: Use CDS1 Completion Date PAYG clients: Use CDS2 Completion Date plus a positive credit check Exclusions: Add-ons like TVs, Direct Drip (DD) units, and promotional items Benchmark/Targets: Based on targets shared by the FP&A team 2. üîÅ Leads Conversion Rate‚Äã Purpose: Measures the percentage of leads generated year-to-date (YTD) that have been successfully converted into sales, based on the sales definitions provided above. Calculation: (Number of Leads Converted to Sales YTD) / (Total Leads Generated YTD) √ó 100% Notes: ‚ÄúConverted‚Äù is based on the country-specific sales logic described in the Sales (YTD) section. Helps assess the effectiveness of the lead-to-sale pipeline across countries. 3. üïí PAR30 (%)‚Äã Purpose: Measures the percentage of active clients whose outstanding balance is 30 days or more past due. Indicates portfolio risk and repayment delays. Calculation: (Outstanding Balance of Accounts >30 Days Past Due) / (Total Portfolio Balance of Active Clients) √ó 100% Notes: Only includes Active Accounts (excluding Arrears, written-off accounts). 4. üö´ FPD Rate (%)‚Äã Purpose: Tracks the portion of the portfolio that is under First Payment Default (FPD) ‚Äî accounts that failed to make the first scheduled payment after activation. Calculation: (Balance of Clients Under FPD) / (Total Portfolio Balance) √ó 100% 5. üíµ Collection Rate (%)‚Äã Purpose: Measures the effectiveness of collections by comparing how much was collected vs. how much was expected. Calculation: (Total Amount Collected) / (Total Amount Expected) √ó 100% 6. üîÑ Pre-Installation Churn Rate (%)‚Äã Purpose: Measures the percentage of accounts that were fully refunded before installation, indicating early customer churn or cancellation. Calculation: (Number of Accounts Fully Refunded Before Installation YTD) / (Total Sales YTD) √ó 100% Notes: Excludes refunds that occurred after installation. Helps monitor pre-delivery customer dropout and operational inefficiencies. 7. üõ†Ô∏è Average Installation Wait Days‚Äã Purpose: Measures the average number of days taken from the date of sale to successful installation, reflecting operational efficiency and customer onboarding experience. Calculation: Average(Date of Installation ‚àí Date of Sale) Notes: For PAYG clients, use Full Deposit Date as the Sale Date. For Cash clients, use Full Payment Date. Installation Date is based on the JSF Date. Last updated: 2025-05-21 Maintainer: Data Team For custom reports or access issues, contact the Data Team via the Data Request Form. üß† Previous Overview Next Kenya üéØ Objective üìà Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) 1. üíº Sales (YTD) 2. üîÅ Leads Conversion Rate 3. üïí PAR30 (%) 4. üö´ FPD Rate (%) 5. üíµ Collection Rate (%) 6. üîÑ Pre-Installation Churn Rate (%) 7. üõ†Ô∏è Average Installation Wait Days

Overview On this page üìä KPIs & Metrics Overview Welcome to the centralized hub for all Metrics and Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) at SunCulture. This space serves as a single source of truth for how we define, calculate, and track key metrics across teams. Whether you're building dashboards, aligning on targets, or digging into performance trends‚Äîthis is where shared definitions live. üìò Definition of Terms‚Äã Metric: A quantifiable measure of business activity (e.g., number of leads, total units sold). KPI (Key Performance Indicator): A critical metric that reflects how well a team or function is achieving strategic goals. ‚ûï All KPIs are metrics, but not all metrics are KPIs. KPIs are the most impactful, decision-driving metrics. üéØ Objectives‚Äã Standardize Business Language: Establish consistent definitions for KPIs and metrics to ensure aligned performance tracking across teams. Promote Consistency & Transparency: Eliminate ambiguity and provide a clear reference point for reporting and decision-making. Enable Self-Service Discovery: Make KPIs and metrics easy to find, understand, and trust. Support Scalable Analytics: Foster a data-informed culture and reduce onboarding friction by documenting critical metrics in one place. üìÅ What‚Äôs Inside‚Äã Metrics are organized by department and functional domain. Each section provides: Topic ‚Äî Thematic focus (e.g., Performance, Productivity) Business Question ‚Äî The core question the metric answers KPI / Metric ‚Äî Name of the measure Calculation ‚Äî How it's computed Benchmark ‚Äî Target or goal (if available) Comments ‚Äî Notes or interpretation tips All entries are displayed in a concise, tabular format for quick consumption. üîó Quick Links‚Äã üõ†Ô∏è Operations‚Äã Sales Credit Supply Chain Operations After Sales Customer Experience Carbon üöÄ Growth‚Äã Business Development üí∞ Finance‚Äã Finance ESG üß™ Product & Engineering‚Äã Product Engineering Data Tech Ops Quality üë• People & Culture‚Äã People & Culture ü§ù External Affairs‚Äã External Affairs üß† Want to suggest a new KPI or update an existing one?
